      "notes": "PINS the \u00a72-resync / ERR_BAD_CRC tension: when a syntactically complete frame (LEN within max_payload, all bytes received) fails CRC, Light replies ERR_BAD_CRC echoing the received SEQ, then rescans per \u00a72 (discard one byte past SOF). This frame contains no interior 0xA5, so exactly one ERROR is emitted. Headers that can't be trusted enough to reply to are the silent-resync cases (see resync-false-sof-huge-len).",
      "pins_open_behavior": true
    },
